Basic Visulaizations¶

The purpose of this notebook is to code basic visulaizations using

  • Matplotlib
  • Seaborn

These visualizations will include:

  • line plot
  • pie chart
  • scatter plot
  • Histogram

The data for this project can be found on the github page and is a small sample of stock prices

Line Chart¶

In [67]:
#call the type of plot, identify the data for the x & y axis,.... 
#....label the line, determine the figsize and linewidth, line color

stock_df.plot(x = "Date", y = "FB", label = "Facebook Stock Price", figsize = (15,10), linewidth = 2, color = 'b')

#label y-axis
plt.ylabel('Price [$]')

#Give a title to graph
plt.title("Facebook Stock Price: Line Plot")

#place the line label (legend)
plt.legend(loc = 'upper left')

#include a grid
plt.grid()
In [66]:
## Multiple lines on one chart
# enter multiple inputs for y axis
stock_df.plot(x = 'Date', y = ['FB', 'TWTR', 'NFLX'], figsize = (15, 10), linewidth = 3)
plt.ylabel('Price')
plt.title('Stock Prices')
plt.legend(loc="upper center")
plt.grid()

plt.figure(figsize = (17,17))
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(stock_df.index, stock_df['FB'], 'r--');
plt.xlabel("# of Days")
plt.ylabel("Stock Price[$]")
plt.title("Stock Price over Days")
plt.grid()
plt.legend(['Facebook price']);

plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(stock_df.index, stock_df['TWTR'], 'b.');
plt.xlabel("# of Days")
plt.ylabel("Stock Price[$]")
plt.title("Stock Price over Days")
plt.grid()

# set the x and y axis
X = daily_return_df['FB']
Y = daily_return_df['NFLX']
# set the figsize
plt.figure(figsize = (10,10))

# call the plot...insert the X and Y values
plt.scatter(X,Y)

# label the graph
plt.xlabel('Facebook')
plt.ylabel('Netflix')
plt.title("Scatter Plot: Stock Prices")

# call to display the plot
plt.show()

In [49]:
#using the mean (average) stock price to generate the pie chart
#create some variables to graph
values = [FB_mean, TWTR_mean, NFLX_mean]
colors = ['g','b','r']
labels = ['Facebook', 'Twitter','Netflix']

# create the pie chart
plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))
plt.pie(values, colors = colors, labels = labels)
plt.title("Average Stock Price");

Histogram Plot¶

Histograms use bars (various heights) to represent data

Each bar groups data into specific ranges (called 'Bins')
